                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-7">
                <p class="food-para">
                    Food sampling is a process used to check that a food is safe and that it does not contain harmful contaminants, or that 
                    it contains only permitted additives at acceptable levels, or that it contains the right levels of key ingredients and its 
                    label declarations are correct, or to know the levels of nutrients present. A food sample is carried out by subjecting the 
                    product to physical analysis.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-7">
                <p class="food-para">
                    !!!!!!!--------------- Another commonly noted problem that affects the usability of irrigation water is regarding the salinity of the water, 
                    its infiltration rate, and the presence of certain harmful toxins such as sodium, chloride, and boron. Thus, the irrigation 
                    water needs to be tested against Ammonium, Nitrate, Arsenic, Cadmium, Calcium, Manganese, Chloride, Copper, Zinc, Electrical 
                    Conductivity, Sodium Adsorption Ratio, and Potassium. ----------------!!!!!
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-3">
                <div class="food-image">
                    <img src="/images/water_pic_2.jpg" alt="food-check-image" width="100%">
